In the backend code, the route `/view_location/<location_id>` is defined to show properties in a selected location, but in the frontend template `dashboard.html` and other templates, the location filter or buttons use the location name (e.g., "Downtown", "Midtown") as the location identifier rather than the `location_id`. This mismatch will cause the filtering by location to fail because the backend expects a `location_id` but the frontend passes a location name string.

