Coding plan:
"### File Structure
```
RealEstate/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── property_search.html
│   ├── property_details.html
│   ├── property_inquiry.html
│   ├── my_inquiries.html
│   ├── my_favorites.html
│   ├── agents.html
│   └── locations.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (property and agent images if any)
│
└── data/
    ├── properties.txt
    ├── locations.txt
    ├── inquiries.txt
    ├── favorites.txt
    └── agents.txt
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It will handle routing, data reading/writing from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and serve the HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic including data management, filtering, and page rendering will be contained here.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the web application pages, corresponding to the eight pages specified in the requirements:
  - `dashboard.html`: Dashboard page layout and elements.
  - `property_search.html`: Property search and filter interface.
  - `property_details.html`: Detailed property information page.
  - `property_inquiry.html`: Inquiry submission form.
  - `my_inquiries.html`: Display of user inquiries and their statuses.
  - `my_favorites.html`: List and management of favorite properties.
  - `agents.html`: Real estate agents directory.
  - `locations.html`: Featured locations listing and sorting.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets such as CSS, JavaScript, and images:
  - `css/styles.css`: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - `js/scripts.js`: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., button actions, filtering UI).
  - `images/`: Folder for property and agent images if applicable.

- **data/**  
  Stores all application data in text files as specified:
  - `properties.txt`: Property listings data.
  - `locations.txt`: Location information.
  - `inquiries.txt`: Property inquiries submitted by users.
  - `favorites.txt`: User favorite properties.
  - `agents.txt`: Real estate agents data.

This structure keeps the application modular and maintainable, with a single backend file for simplicity and clear separation of frontend templates and static resources."

